<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 4:47PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Jefferson County through 530 PM MDT...
At 447 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Warm Springs, or 14 miles northwest of Butte, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Boulder, Basin, Wickes and Elk Park.
This includes Interstate 15 between mile markers 137 and 171.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
